The paper deals with graph theory and width parameters, which are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the treewidth, pathwidth, branchwidth, clique-width, and tree-depth of graphs, which are topics in graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of graph width parameters is also relevant to theoretical computer science (cs.GT) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
